- HDI (Human Development Index) is a composite statistic of life expectancy, education, and per capita income indicators; 
- GDP (Gross Domestic Product) is the total value of goods and services produced within a country's borders; 
- GDP per capita is the total output of a country divided by its population; 
- High education typically refers to post-secondary education, including but not limited to universities and colleges.

- 'dark days' refers to the number of suicides; 
- 'country shrouded in darkness' and 'land of eagles' are metaphors for Albania, as Albania is sometimes referred to as the 'Land of Eagles' due to its national symbol being the golden double-headed eagle; 
- 'at the dawn of time' implies the year 0, which can be interpreted as the starting point of the dataset or the initial year of recording statistics.
